  "title": "Configure calls onSearchStateChange and locks up JS thread",
  "body": "Bug: What is the current behavior?\r\n\r\nConfigure calls onSearchStateChanged nonstop and locks up the browser until a callstack exceeded error happens.\r\n\r\n\r\nWhat project are you opening an issue for?\r\n\r\nreact-instantsearch\r\nWhat is the version you are using? Always use the latest one before opening a bug issue.\r\n\r\nv3.1.0\r\n\r\nMy guess is it triggers a render, and configure is rendered again, calls search state change again. It should just trigger it if the current configure object is different so this doesnt happen.\r\n\r\nlast issue: #1950",
